<span id="freeTextContainer6411284422933798308">Perfect book to teach inferring to young readers. Cleary says so much about Leigh without explicitly saying it in his early letters to Henshaw. The growth and change in him as the letters turn into a journal is evident to growing readers. Leigh&apos;s story is a sad one, but one many of my students can relate to even today, making the book somewhat timeless. </span>
