<span id="freeTextContainer9311847898082146968">This is the first book I ever read for fun. When I was in 4th grade, I stole this book from my school, and I remember really loving it. After that, I hated reading until college. I was organizing my bookshelves and found this little yellow gem. I have to admit I was behind on my goodreads reading challenge and wanted something I could read in a day. I also remember seeing a movie in high school and a character in the movie said that it was their favorite book! I remember thinking “hey I’ve read </span>
  <span id="freeText9311847898082146968" style="display:none">This is the first book I ever read for fun. When I was in 4th grade, I stole this book from my school, and I remember really loving it. After that, I hated reading until college. I was organizing my bookshelves and found this little yellow gem. I have to admit I was behind on my goodreads reading challenge and wanted something I could read in a day. I also remember seeing a movie in high school and a character in the movie said that it was their favorite book! I remember thinking “hey I’ve read that!” <br /><br />This book is simple, and heartfelt, and calming. I still love it. It wasn’t what I expected. It was sad, and I didn’t remember anything about it. There is a special place in my heart for this little yellow book! :)</span>
